project_descr: Support to Human Security in Eastern Sudan - Phase II

donor_name: DEPT OF FOR AFF & INTL TRADE GOV CANADA
outputs.output_descr:
The Support to Human Security Project in Eastern Sudan phase II aimed to address and
respond to security needs in the three states of Kassala, Gedaref and Red Sea. As part of support to security reforms and demobilization needs in Eastern Sudan 1,700 demobilized   soldiers from the Eastern Front were  provided with a  3 months reintegration package of food (ration  for family of 5 ), 700 ex-combatants were enrolled in  an  individual counseling programmes and  173 ex-combatants were provided with   agricultural , livestock and small business projects (UNDP commitment to the  economic reintegration of Easter Front ex-combatants) .

project_title: support to human security in eastern sudan - phase ii
